 <section class="sg-block sg-section-helper-condensable-condense-">
      <div class="sg-text">
        <h3 id="helper-condensable-condense-" class="sg">HELPER - Condensable (Condense)</h3>
        <p class="sg">
          <code class="sg">.condensable.large .condense</code>- This pattern allows for responsive reduction of content. Content tagged with
          <code class="sg">.condense</code>will turn to display:none when it passes the below the break point. On the container element add &apos;.condensable&apos; and set the break point where you want it by adding the class
          <code class="sg">.small</code>,
          <code class="sg">.medium</code>, or
          <code class="sg">.large</code>. !! Single word reduction requires adding
          <code class="sg">condensable-word</code>see example below.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sg-example">
        <div class="sg-canvas">
          <h2>
            Condensable Sub-line
            <span class="sub-line condensable large">
              <span class="condense">The full word is only seen on large screens.</span>It only says Super below on smaller screens</span>
            <span class="sub-line condensable condensable-word large">Super
              <span class="condense">califragilisticexpialidocious</span>
            </span>
          </h2>
